    {
      "instruction": "<p>After an initial 15 min, remove the<strong> parcel[s]</strong> from the oven</p><p>Return the tray[s] to the oven and cook the <strong>potatoes </strong>for a further 5-10 min or until golden and crisp</p><p>While the potatoes are in the oven, add the <strong>softened pepper</strong>, <strong>garlic</strong>, <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>ground smoked</strong> <strong>paprika</strong>, <strong>flaked</strong> <strong>almonds</strong> and the juice of <strong>half</strong> your <strong>lemon[s]</strong> to a food processor</p><p>Season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong>, then<strong> </strong>blitz until you have a coarse paste – this is your <strong>romesco sauce</strong></p>",
